==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Imperium
<hw>Im*pe"ri*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu>pl.
<plw>Imperia</plw> <pr>(#)</pr></plu>. <ety>[L. See
<er>Empire</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Supreme power; absolute
dominion; empire.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>The right to command, which
includes the right to employ the force of the state to enforce the laws.
It is one of the principal attributes of the executive power.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Imperiwigged</ent>⟦br⟧
